    $\mathcal{A}$ is a $\mathbf{F}_p$-algebra of the following form:
    For $p=2$, \[\mathcal{A}_*=P(\xi_0,\xi_1,\xi_2,\xi_3,\ldots)\]
    where $|\xi_i|= 2^i-1$.  For $p>2$,
    \[\mathcal{A}_*=P(\xi_0,\xi_1,\xi_2,\ldots)\otimes
      E(\tau_1,\tau_2,\ldots)\] where $|\xi_i|=2(p^i-1)$ and
    $|\tau_i|=2p^i-1$, and where $\xi_0=1$ in both cases.

